a moderate aftershock measuring 42 on the richter scale struck 
at 144 am followed by a second stronger aftershock that 
measured 45 at 853 am the usgs said 
the openended richter scale is a measure of ground motion 
recorded on a seismograph each increase of one number means a 
tenfold increase in ground motion 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
6 severe damage a 7 reading is a major earthquake capable of 
widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable of 
tremendous damage 
the san francisco earthquake of 1906 which occurred before the 
richter scale was devised has been estimated at 83 on the scale 
