thursday and friday such a panel is appointed every four years to 
examine issues affecting the social security medicare and medicaid 
programs 
ms steelman said the council hopes to issue a draft report on 
health care financing by july 1990 and recommendations on the 
financing and role of social security benefits by december 1990 a 
final report to congress and the department of health and human 
services is due in january 1991 
ms steelman said the current medicare system is projected to 
be insolvent by early in the next century before the baby boom has 
even begun to enter retirement 
the smaller ranks of people in the generations following the 
baby boom will make it difficult for them to finance benefits for 
the bulge in retirees that precedes them she said 
