surgical instruments test tubes and clothing from the earthen 
basement of the 1835 building 
i can think of no other archaeological find in the us 
remotely like it said robert l blakely a georgia state 
university anthropologist there may be other medical colleges 
that have things like this in their cellars but they havent been 
discovered 
records by george m newton dean of faculty at the college in 
the mid1800s indicate that graverobbing was a booming business 
until 1887 when the laws changed 
graverobbing was often the only way medical schools could get 
around laws that equated human dissection with desecration 
newton bought 2000 gallons of whiskey in the 1850s and made 
references to transactions such as joe for subject 10 
the subjects were preserved in newtons whiskey until the 
time came for them to provide medical students vital lessons on the 
basics of human anatomy 
the bodies were mostly blacks because when you have a large 
