<TEXT>
consumers have to be given some credit for the 
manner in which they have behaved in recent months counting their 
money and retreating from high prices and borrowing costs 
they beat the carmakers at their own game declining to pay full 
price and forcing them to offer rebates and discounts in order to 
cut inventories they have been slow to buy bigticket appliances 
they are cautious 
they have slowed their acquisition of credit in part because 
bank card borrowing comes at exorbitant rates these days and 
lenders refuse to come down in line with other rates 
consumer credit in june did rise but the tendency to go into 
debt has receded over the past year in may the annual growth rate 
was 73 percent but in june it dropped to 51 percent 
the tendency of consumers to watch their dollars does seem 
contradicted by one area of credit bank card credit has continued 
to rise however the disinclination of banks to lower their rates 
215 percent annual interest isnt uncommon that consumer 
resistance so clear in other ways seems almost certain 
buyers also slowed the rate of increase in home prices by 
declining to chase the market theyve actually forced prices down 
in some areas a rarity buyers now have the uupper hand in most of 
the country 
they are showing their good sense in other ways too borrowing 
costs on homes are falling and many homeowners are planning to 
refinance at lower rates again its a consumers market banks 
are advertising for customers 
meanwhile consumers have been strengthening their cash 
position they have improved their savings personal savings as a 
percentage of income in june rose to 59 percent from 54 percent 
in may and the total of 2241 billion was the second highest ever 
personal income has been improving too the improvement hasnt 
been sharp but it has been healthy especially since inflation has 
been relatively restrained both low inflation and rising income 
reinforce higher savings 
these and other factors including an unusually strong 
employment situation put the consumer in a strong position as the 
economy slows in a sense consumers are in a position to dictate 
in many areas of the economy 
the situation is in stark contrast to conditions that prevailed 
in the 1970s when the consumer was on the run 
so desperate where buyers in that decade that they purchased in 
anticipation of price increases and in so doing drove prices even 
higher they were panicked convinced that they could save by 
buying in advance of need 
the situation today is reversed buyers are more inclined to sit 
and wait convinced that waiting is the way to a better deal they 
are patient rather than frantic they are making the seller come to 
them 
it is a rather rare situation but it is one that might help to 
correct a slur on consumers that they are mere puppets 
manipulated by clever marketers if they can hold their ground they 
might change some minds 
