<TEXT>
here are a few financial safety tips for travelers according to 
industry experts and consumer groups 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
keep most of your money in travelers checks theyre safer than 
cash because the issuer gives full or partial refunds for lost or 
stolen checks checks in foreign currency may be available at a 
major bank at official exchange rates usually without service fees 
carry us dollars and the currency of whatever country youre 
visiting us money should be in small denominations to handle 
minor expenses such as tips or parking before or after departure 
bring at least one major credit card for either identification 
or purchases two is better since not all cards are universally 
accepted but leave the cards you dont expect to use at home 
try to buy all your travel tickets through a credit card if 
possible its often easier to get replacement tickets and many 
creditcard companies provide limited travel insurance 
after charging meals souvenirs or other items destroy all 
charge card carbons immediately 
double check your credit card bill to ensure all purchases are 
listed correctly and contact your bank or creditcard company 
immediately if theres an incorrect expense cardholders are liable 
for up to 50 of unauthorized purchases before they report a card 
stolen or lost but theyre not liable for any purchases after a 
report is filed 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

