<TEXT>
compagnie industrielle will resist the largest 
takeover bid ever attempted in france a 25 billion offer from a 
former ally its president said wednesday 
jeanmarc vernes head of the holding company under attack from 
compagnie financiere de suez a parisbased bank holding company 
declined to discuss what allies he might be lining up for the fight 
suez won a long and difficult takeover battle last year with 
italian financier carlo de benedetti for control of the huge 
belgian holding company societe generale de belgique 
the prize in the takeover battle is groupe victoire frances 
secondbiggest insurance group suez which traces its corporate 
history to the financing of the suez canal more than a century ago 
currently shares control of groupe victoire with compagnie 
industrielle 
the paris stock exchange said in a statement that suez proposes 
to offer the equivalent of 2030 per share for the 815 percent of 
compagnie industrielle stock it does not already own that would 
value the target companys equity at 3 billion and the suez offer 
would total about 25 billion 
vernes was quoted by the french news agency agence francepresse 
as saying he would make no statement until the hostile takeover bid 
by suez has been approved by stock market regulatory authorities 
the regulatory decision is expected on aug 18 and if the bid 
is approved stockholders then would have a month to decide whether 
to sell at that price 
trading in compagnie industrielle stock has been frozen since 
friday it was last quoted on the paris bourse at the equivalent of 
1525 per share 
the price of suez shares fell to 5555 a share from 5766 on 
wednesday in active trading 
groupe victoire was originally part of the suez holdings but 
when it appeared likely that the socialists would win the 1981 
elections suezs president at the time jack frances quietly 
transferred control to the holding company compagnie industrielle 
which he controlled along with allies including the dassault family 
when the new socialist government indeed nationalized suez along 
with other banks and industrial firms it was surprised to find the 
groupe victoire insurance company no longer a suez subsidiary 
although suez did retain a minority interest partly direct and 
partly through compagnie industrielle 
the conservative government elected in 1986 sold suez to private 
investors but its new owners have had uneasy relations with 
vernes who succeeded frances as head of compagnie industrielle 
