<TEXT>
us authorities will have to borrow tens of 
billions of dollars from other countries to help bail out failed 
savings and loans institutions dollars foreigners will someday use 
to compete for scarcer goods in this country an economist 
predicted wednesday 
the bill president bush signed wednesday authorizes borrowing 
50 billion over the next 26 months the total cost of the bailout 
will be far higher because of interest costs 
foreigners already buy future claims on this country at a rate 
of 10 billion a month through their purchases of american bonds 
shares real estate and other property 
americans do not save enough of their own money to pay for the 
things they want from foreigners now so the needed money has to be 
lent to this country from abroad 
unfortunately people in government focus on shortterm 
problems and not on the long term said matthew b canzoneri 
professor of economics at georgetown university 
im a babyboomer in the long run therell be fewer people 
in this country to produce goods to support me in my old age the 
same is true of mr yamaguchi in japan and the japanese 
population is getting older faster than ours is 
canzoneri sees japanese and other foreigners wanting to cash in 
their loans and investments and use the dollars to buy up american 
goods at a time when fewer american goods will be produced in 
proportion to the us population all that money chasing fewer 
goods will run up prices lower living standards and bring 
pressures to cut pensions in this country he predicted 
canzoneri also predicts additional government borrowing will 
cause shortterm problems 
lenders in wall street may get jittery he said that 
would drive up interest rates that will increase the cost of the 
federal governments deficit then there would be pressure on the 
federal reserve system to push interest rates down that would mean 
even more borrowing and the threat of inflation 
