harris corp is seeking buyers for its 
data communications and personal computer divisions after an 852 
million restructuring intended to streamline operations the 
defense and aerospace contractor said wednesday 
the company which began to scale down in the mid 1980s is now 
organized into four major sectors electronics semiconductors 
communications and lanier worldwide inc the new name of its 
harris3m international division 
the businesses we are selling are outside the mainstream of 
our future interests and their sale will release assets and other 
resources for our core businesses said john hartley 
chairman and chief executive officer in a press release 
the release did not name a price for the two divisions or 
whether any companies have expressed interest in them 
the restructuring cost dropped net income for the year ended 
june 30 nearly 80 percent while sales and pershare profit rose 
for the 12 months ended june 30 the melbournebased company 
reported net income of 213 million or 55 cents a share on sales 
of 22 billion compared with net income of 1005 million or 
250 a share on sales of 18 billion for the previous fiscal 
year 
in the fourth quarter the restructuring costs led to a net loss 
of 52 million on sales of 7683 million compared with net income 
of 18 million or 5 cents a share on sales of 4718 million in 
the yearago period 
